# Integration Stack Rules

## Intent
Define safe integration contracts for Clerk auth, GetStream chat, and Sentry observability.

## Clerk Rules
- Use Clerk as source of truth for authentication and session identity.
- Map Clerk identity to internal user profile through explicit adapter layer.
- Enforce server-side authorization checks independent of client claims.

## GetStream Rules
- Use shared client wrappers for Stream token issuance and channel operations.
- Gate mini-app command operations with policy checks before Stream-side actions.
- Log Stream access purpose and command context in audit events.
- Enforce Maker-tier capacity controls and fallback behavior from [110-stream-maker-tier-rules.mdc](110-stream-maker-tier-rules.mdc).

## Sentry Rules
- Sentry is required for error monitoring across web and mobile.
- Apply default PII scrubbing and deny-list sensitive fields before event send.
- Correlate Sentry events with request/trace identifiers without storing sensitive payload bodies.

## Prohibited
- Calling third-party SDKs directly from feature modules when shared wrappers exist.
- Enabling verbose data capture modes in production without risk approval.